com.google.crypto.tink.internal

Interface PrimitiveConstructor.PrimitiveConstructionFunction<KeyT extends Key,PrimitiveT>

  • Enclosing class:
    PrimitiveConstructor<KeyT extends Key,PrimitiveT>

    public static interface PrimitiveConstructor.PrimitiveConstructionFunction<KeyT extends Key,PrimitiveT>
    A function which creates a Primitive object.

    This interface exists only so we have a type we can reference in PrimitiveConstructor.create(com.google.crypto.tink.internal.PrimitiveConstructor.PrimitiveConstructionFunction<KeyT, PrimitiveT>, java.lang.Class<KeyT>, java.lang.Class<PrimitiveT>). Users should not use this directly; see the explanation in PrimitiveConstructor.create(com.google.crypto.tink.internal.PrimitiveConstructor.PrimitiveConstructionFunction<KeyT, PrimitiveT>, java.lang.Class<KeyT>, java.lang.Class<PrimitiveT>).
